The tagline reads This robot helps kids learn social skills" - that is clearly overselling the robot or underselling social skills..."

Our new Robot of the Week is QTrobot from @LuxAI_SA . It's designed for therapists and educators, especially for helping children with autism spectrum disorder. QTrobot sure is a cutie https:// robots.ieee.org/robots/qtrobot/

I would suggest that if your proposed method of communication for autistic consultants is via Skype, you have a lot more to learn about autism than you realise - and that you need #ActuallyAutistic people involved ASAP.

Actually we had adults with autism doing internship in our team and helping us to develop QTs applications! We know that we need the opinion of more adults with autism and if you are interested or know someone who is interested we would be very happy to have skype calls.

Ah, autism professionals" and the dreaded "organisations for autism". But no autistic adults or even autistic children apart from participants. And it's limited to "feedback", you don't employ or contract anyone who's autistic in your project for people who are autistic."

and anyone with autism or with a child with autism is very appreciated to share experiences and opinions with us, so hopefully we can build something which is more effective and practical to support children.

Actually since the beginning of our activities we had a great collaboration with organizations for autism and the feedback and opinion of children as well as autism professional were the foundation of our development.
Though this would appear to be yet another project focused on *autism* where there is a total lack of participation or input from anyone who's actually *autistic*. @LuxAI_SA ???
